      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/30/5281",
      "text": [
        ": \"إِنَّ فِي لِسَانِ اَلْأَخْرَسِ وَ عَيْنِ اَلْأَعْمَى وَ ذَكَرِ اَلْخَصِيِّ اَلْحُرِّ وَ أُنْثَيَيْهِ ثُلُثَ اَلدِّيَةِ وَ فِي ذَكَرِ اَلْغُلاَمِ اَلدِّيَةَ كَامِلَةً\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.5281 - Ibn Mahbub narrated from Abu Ayyub from Buraid Al-Ijli from Abu Jafar Imam Muhammad ibn Ali Al-Baqir (as) who said:\n\"For the tongue of a mute person, the eye of a blind person, and the private parts and testicles of a free eunuch, one-third of the full blood money (diyya) is due.\nHowever, for the private part of a young boy, the full blood money is due.\""
        ]
      }
    },
